main event: A bright, self-luminous object was observed in Davidsonville, Maryland, on February 9, 1967, moving in a southeasterly direction.
interesting points: The object was described as circular and emitted flashing colors (red, white, green)., The sighting duration was approximately 60 seconds., The object was observed at an altitude of 100-300 feet., The witness, Mrs. John Doe, reported no noise associated with the object., Witness Mr. Edwin C. Piratzky noted the object moved in an erratic manner before disappearing.
witness description: Mrs. John Doe (housewife) and Mr. Edwin C. Piratzky (resident of Davidsonville)
